{{Infobox Coin | Country = United States | Denomination = Dollar | Value = 1 | Unit = [[U.S. Dollar]] | Mass = ? | Diameter = ? | Thickness = ? | Edge = Reeded | Composition = 90%[[Silver|Ag]] / 10%[[Copper|Cu]]? | Years of Minting = 1983 | Catalog Number = [[Standard Catalog of World Coins|KM# 209]] | Obverse = Olympiad1983.jpg | Obverse Design = Discus Thrower, In God We Trust, Liberty,Los Angeles, XXIII Olympiad,Olympic rings,1983, S (mint mark), EJ (designers Initials)| Obverse Designer = [[Elizabeth Jones (engraver)|Elizabeth Jones]] | Obverse Design Date = 1983? | Reverse = Olympiad2.jpg | Reverse Design = United States of America, One Dollar, ''[[E Pluribus Unum]]'', a [[bald eagle]], EJ-JIII (designers initials and again J with a E at a 90 degree turn) | Reverse Designer = [[Elizabeth Jones (engraver)|Elizabeth Jones]] | Reverse Design Date = ? | }}
The '''Los Angeles XXIII Olympiad dollar''' was a [[Commemorative coin|commemorative]] one [[dollar]] coin minted by the United States to commemorate the [[1984 Summer Olympics|1984 Summer Olympic games]] held in Los Angeles. 174,074 of these coins were minted in [[Uncirculated coin|Uncirculated]] or [[Proof coinage|Proof]] finishes by all three of the United States mints: [[Philadelphia Mint]], [[Denver Mint]], [[San Francisco Mint]]. The coin was made of 90% [[silver]] and 10% [[copper]].
{{Coinage (United States)}}
{{DEFAULTSORT:Los Angeles Xxiii Olympiad Dollar}} [[Category:Currency introduced in 1983]] [[Category:Modern United States commemorative coins]] [[Category:United States silver coins]] [[Category:1984 Summer Olympics]] [[Category:Birds on coins]] [[Category:Sports in art]]

{{Infobox football club |clubname = MHSK |image = |fullname = MHSK futbol klubi |nickname = |founded = c.{{Start date|1945}} |dissolved = {{Start date and age|2001}} |ground = [[MHSK Stadium]] |capacity = 17,000 |chairman = |Director = |manager = |league = [[Uzbekistan First League]] |season = [[Uzbekistan First League|1999]] |position = 6th }}
'''MHSK''' ({{lang-uz|Марказий Ҳарбий спорт клуби|translit=Markaziy Harbiy Sport Klubi}}) is a [[Uzbekistan]]i [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Tashkent]]. Its abbreviation means Army Central Sports Club, similar to the Soviet equivalent CSKA.
==History== The year of establishment is unknown, yet the club participated in the Soviet competitions since 1946. Until 1988 it played as part of the Soviet Armed Forces sports club which often was changing its name. Since 1955 it was named as SKA Tashkent. In 1989 it was transformed into a junior squad as Regional School of Higher Sports Mastery, SKA-RShVSM Tashkent. With the [[fall of the Soviet Union]] in 1992, the club became a farm club of [[FC Pakhtakor Tashkent]] as Pakhtakor-79 Tashkent. Since 1993 and until 2001 the club played as MHSK Tashkent.
MHSK Tashkent played 7 seasons in [[Uzbek League]]: 1992–1998. In that time club won championship in 1997 and runner-up in 1995 [[Uzbek Cup]]. One year later in 1998 season, club finished [[1998 Uzbek League|16th]] and relegated to lower division. In 1999–2000 club played in [[Uzbekistan First League]]. Before the start of 2001 season in First League, MHSK officially withdrew from competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tableso/oez01.html|title=First League (Second Level) 2001|publisher=rsssf.com|accessdate=|date =}}</ref>
===Name changes history=== * until 1992: Umid * 1992: Pakhtakor-79 * 1993: Binokor * 1993—2001: MHSK
==Honours== * '''[[Uzbek League]] champion: 1''' ** [[1997 Uzbek League|1997]] * '''[[Uzbek Cup]] runner-up: 1''' ** 1995
