[[File:Saida International Stadium with beachgoers.jpg|thumb|right|The stadium in its beachside setting – August 2009]] '''Saida International Stadium''' ({{Lang-ar|إستاد صيدا الدولي}}) is a 22,600 capacity [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Saida, Lebanon|Saida]] (Sidon, Zidon), [[Lebanon]]. The stadium was built on the expanded grounds of the old Saida Municipal Stadium, as one of the venues to host matches during the [[2000 AFC Asian Cup]] that was held in [[Lebanon]]. It is currently mostly used for local and international [[football (soccer)|football]] matches. The stadium also has athletics facilities.
==Location==
The stadium is located at the main northern entrance of the city. Saida International Stadium, built over the sea, is the closest stadium to the sea in the world.
