{{Infobox sport overview | boxwidth = 250 | title = Surfing in South Africa | image = | imagesize = | image_alt = <!-- alt text, which will be seen when hovering over the image --> | caption = | union = [[Surfing South Africa]] | country = South Africa | sport = Surfing | noncountry = <!-- other country this country represents --> | teamlabel1 = <!-- overrides the "National team" label with custom label --> | nationalteam = [[South Africa at the Olympics|South Africa Olympics team]] | teamlabel2 = <!-- overrides the "Representative team" label with customer label --> | repteam = <!-- overrides the representative team link, requires full wikitext syntax --> | nickname = <!-- nicknames --> | first = | registered = | clubs = | national_list = | intl_list = [[Surfing at the 2020 Summer Olympics|Summer Olympics]] | match = | league = }}
'''Surfing in South Africa''' began in Durban in the 1940s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=mYBtMajLAaAC&pg=PA161&lpg=PA161&dq=history+of+surfing+in+south+africa&source=bl&ots=MaBHjNjCaD&sig=uOQe8O4dHSkSRfwxTg3dmPTRIgU&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj18cmO5tjLAhXBExoKHVTLDfAQ6AEITDAJ#v=onepage&q=history%20of%20surfing%20in%20south%20africa&f=false |title=Sports around the World: History, Culture, and Practice [4 volumes&#93;: History ... |page=161 |website=Books.google.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=JRjcAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA31&lpg=PA31&dq=black%20surfers&source=bl&ots=iqF_6ZawQI&sig=u_O78UIgf5vdB4dKHZjfcMOWd0I&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiq9rWoqt7QAhXsKMAKHUD_BPk4MhDoAQgqMAM#v=onepage&q=black%20surfers&f=false|title=Sport Past and Present in South Africa: (Trans)forming the Nation|first1=Scarlett|last1=Cornelissen|first2=Albert|last2=Grundlingh|date=13 September 2013|publisher=Routledge|accessdate=6 December 2016|via=Google Books}}</ref>
By 1965 the South African Surfing Association was formed. In recent years surfing associations have tried to encourage more black South Africans to take up surfing.<ref>{{cite news|title= Waves for Change: How surf therapy is helping South Africa's most deprived children|publisher= [[The Independent|Independent]]|date=|url= https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/africa/waves-for-change-how-surf-therapy-is-helping-south-africas-most-deprived-children-10464362.html|accessdate=2016-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Dr Dude rides waves of SA's surfing history|publisher= [[The Times (South Africa)|Times]]|date=|url= http://www.timeslive.co.za/sundaytimes/stnews/2015/04/05/dr-dude-rides-waves-of-sa-s-surfing-history|accessdate=2016-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Surfing in South Africa Celebrates 50th Anniversary|publisher= [[International Surfing Association|ISA]]|date=|url= https://www.isasurf.org/surfing-in-south-africa-celebrates-50th-anniversary/|accessdate=2016-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Reclaiming the waves: South Africa's new surfing heroes|publisher= CNN|date=|url= http://edition.cnn.com/2015/09/22/africa/south-africa-black-surfers-ayuvile-ndamase/|accessdate=2016-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=wNR_ZMZCt4kC&pg=PA398&lpg=PA398&dq=history+of+surfing+in+south+africa&source=bl&ots=3BdJQxDPft&sig=eG9IxBgkExZG3FAkvnPEAmU4n2Q&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj18cmO5tjLAhXBExoKHVTLDfAQ6AEIPTAG#v=onepage&q=history%20of%20surfing%20in%20south%20africa&f=false |title=The History of Surfing |author=Matt Warshaw |page=398 |website=Books.google.co.uk |date=2011-04-29 |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/foreign/content/2016/s4499198.htm|title=South Africa - Freedom Riders - Foreign Correspondent - ABC|publisher=|accessdate=6 December 2016}}</ref>
==Famous surf spots==
===[[Muizenberg]]=== This beach is the home of surfing in South Africa and arguably the oldest surfing town in Africa. Let alone South Africa. Heather Price is considered to be the first ever person recorded to stand-up surf with a photo appearing in a local newspaper in 1919. The modern surfing movement in South Africa was in essence founded by a women, who was born in Zimbabwe.
===[[Jeffreys Bay]]=== Jeffreys Bay is one of the five most famous [[surfing]] destinations (no.2 on one "[http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/30/travel/50-surf-spots/ best in the world]" surfing list) in the world and hosts the annual [[Billabong (clothing)|Billabong Pro]] [[ASP World Tour]] surfing event at Super Tubes during July. [[File:JBay-Surfing at supertubes-001.jpg|thumb|Surfing JBay]]
===St Francis Bay=== A right hand point wave at [[St. Francis Bay]] was first idolised and promoted in the cult classic surf movie ''[[The Endless Summer]]'' in the 1960s {{commonscat}}
